elements.description:
*Note:** This is closed software and you can't use it in your projects unless
you are a Mulesoft employee working on internall project.

A set of Anypoint icons to be used with ARC web components.
They occupy the same namespace as ARC icons set.

Use them in bower.json like this:

```
"dependencies": {
  ...
  "arc-icons": "advanced-rest-clinet/anypoint-icons"
}
```
Be sure to put it to the end of the dependencies so it won't be replaced with original
ARC icons by other comnponent.

Include library into the document / element:
```
<link rel="import" href="../arc-icons/arc-icons.html">
```

To use an icon from this set you should prefix `iron-icon` with the `arc`, followed by a colon, ":", and then the icon id.

Example using the directions-bus icon from the maps icon set:
```
<iron-icon icon="arc:add"></iron-icon>
```

*Note:** This is closed software and you can't use it in your projects unless
you are a Mulesoft employee working on internall project.

A set of Anypoint icons to be used in web components.

Include library into the document / element:
```
<link rel="import" href="../anypoint-icons/anypoint-icons.html">
```

To use an icon from this set you should prefix `iron-icon` with the `anypoint`, followed by a colon, ":", and then the icon id.

Example using the directions-bus icon from the maps icon set:
```
<iron-icon icon="anypoint:application"></iron-icon>
```
